            <pb n="130" facs="#f0001"/>
            <div n="1">
                <head>
                    <hi rendition="#k">Baron de Humboldt.</hi>
                </head>
                <p>&#x2014;The death of M. William de<lb break="yes"/>Humboldt, formerly Prussian Minister, has been an-<lb break="no"/>nounced in the journals. The following is an extract<lb break="yes"/>from a letter dated April 10, which M. Alexander Hum-<lb break="no"/>boldt, the celebrated traveller, has written to M. Arago, of<lb break="yes"/>the <hi rendition="#i">Institute:</hi>&#x2014;</p>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <p>&#x201C;I had the misfortune to lose my brother on the even-<lb break="no"/>ing before last. I am in the deepest affliction. In our<lb break="yes"/>greatest sorrows we think of those who are the most dear<lb break="yes"/>to us; I feel a little relieved in writing to you. ..........<lb break="yes"/>We saw he was dying, for ten days. His weakness had<lb break="yes"/>cruelly increased for several weeks; a constant trembling<lb break="yes"/>took place in all his members, but his mind retained its<lb break="yes"/>full energy. He was always writing; he leaves two works<lb break="yes"/>nearly finished; one upon the languages of the Indian<lb break="yes"/>Archipelago, derived from the Sanscrit; the other upon<lb break="yes"/>the origin and the philosophy of languages in general.<lb break="yes"/>These works will be published. My brother has left his<lb break="yes"/>manuscripts, some works he had begun, and his previous<lb break="yes"/>collection of books, to the public library. He died of an<lb break="yes"/>inflammation of the chest, and he watched the progress<lb break="yes"/>of the disease with an afflicting sagacity; he was endowed<lb break="yes"/>with superior intelligence, and with a mind full of ele-<lb break="no"/>vation and nobleness; I remain sadly isolated. I hope<lb break="yes"/>that I shall, at last, have the happiness of embracing you<lb break="yes"/>this year. ........</p>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <p>&#x201C;Tegel, near Berlin.&#x201D;</p>
            </div>
